===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|en|colour||Commonwealth|Ireland}} (see the [[#Usage notes|usage notes]] below)

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|colour}}, {{m|enm|color}}, borrowed from {{der|en|xno|colur}}, from {{der|en|fro|colour}}, {{m|fro|color}}, from {{der|en|la|color}}. {{doublet|en|couleur}}.

Displaced {{noncog|en|blee}}, {{noncog|enm|blee|t=color}}, from {{noncog|ang|blÄ“o}}. Also partially replaced {{noncog|ang|hÄ«ew||color}} and its descendants ({{noncog|en|hue}}), which is less often used in this sense.

The spelling ''color'' was popularized in modern American English by {{w|Noah Webster}}, to match the spelling of the word's Latin etymon{{,}} and make all American spellings of the derivatives consistent (''colorimeter'',  ''coloration'', ''colorize'', ''colorless'', etc).

