#: {{ux|en|'''Color''' has been a sensitive issue in many societies.}}
# {{lb|en|medicine}} Skin color, noted as normal, [[jaundiced]], [[cyanotic]], [[flush]], [[mottled]], [[pale]], or [[ashen]] as part of the [[skin signs]] assessment.
# A [[flushed]] appearance of blood in the face; redness of complexion.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1864|author=Sir Henry Stewart Cunningham|title=Late Laurels|volume=1-2|page=117
|passage={{...}} her very embarrassment wore a graceful air; her high '''colour''' had softened down to a warm, delicate tint; and her dress, which looked beautifully new and fresh, was in good taste, and showed her off to advantage.}}
