# Conveying color, as opposed to shades of gray.
#: {{ux|en|'''Color''' television and movies were considered a great improvement over black and white.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1977|author=w:John Cheever|title=w:Falconer|series=A Borzoi Book|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:Alfred A. Knopf|Alfred A[braham] Knopf]]|page=209|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/falconer00chee/page/209/mode/1up|isbn=978-0-394-48347-4|passage=I took my TV over on the first trip. I got a beauty. It's four years old, '''color''', but when I had a little snow and asked the repairman to come in, he told me never, never turn this set in for a new one.}}

