==Latin==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|la|colÅs||archaic}}

===Etymology===
{{root|la|ine-pro|*á¸±el- (cover)}}
From earlier {{m|la|colÅs}} (genitive {{m|la||colÅris}}), from {{inh|la|itc-pro|*kelÅs}}, from {{der|la|ine-pro|*á¸±el-|t=to hide, conceal}}.<ref>{{R:itc:EDL|page=126|head=color}}</ref> The nominative singular changed to {{m|la|color}} in Classical times by analogy with the oblique forms, where /r/ had regularly developed from an original intervocalic /s/.

